<HEADLINE>Clearance for airport plans</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>2</EDITION>
<PAGE>9</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>974897153</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
EDINBURGH Airport has been given the go-ahead for a #4m expansion which is
expected to be completed before its busy summer season takes off.
Scottish Airports yesterday announced that domestic and international
facilities at the terminal are set to be expanded during the winter and a new
centralised security area created.
Departure lounges will be enlarged and the international duty-free shop is to
be extended, along with plans for a new bookstall and bureau-de-change.
A spokeswoman for Scottish Airports said: ``This is the first stage of the #20m
development of Edinburgh Airport's terminal facilities over the next decade.''
More than #14m has already been spent in the last four years at the airport,
which is thought to be the fastest growing within the company's group - with an
annual average passenger growth of 10%.
The increase is part of a continuing trend which saw the airport handle more
than three million passengers for the first time in 1994, and which is set to
continue in 1996, with Direct Holidays announcing it is to fly passengers from
Edinburgh to 11 new holiday destinations from next summer.
</TEXT>
