<HEADLINE>I couldn't be bothered</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>1</EDITION>
<PAGE>8</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>974897159</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
SHARON, aged 15, is a fourth-year pupil who spoiled her attendance record with
a period of regular truancy earlier this session. She is extremely quiet and
reticent and has difficulty in rationalising her motives.
I missed the odd day in Primary 7 but there was really nothing else until well
into first year. Even then it was only a few times, and half-days at that. I
couldn't be bothered coming into school. I came in for the mornings, then just
walked about the town in the afternoon or looked in on friends. In the second
year I just took one day off, and three or four days in third year.
My big sister did a bit of dogging as well. It wasn't difficult. The teacher
didn't bother about absence notes at that time. It really got bad this year. I
must have taken 20 or 30 days off between August and October. The house was
empty, everybody was out at work.
I can't really explain it. Maybe it was because my sister left school and got a
job. That made me want to leave as well. I'll leave as soon as possible. I
would like to be a nursery nurse, but I don't think I'll do well enough for
that.
The school didn't chase me up for notes, because they knew I was dogging it
anyway. The attendance officer talked to my sister and gave her a monitoring
slip which was supposed to be filled up. Then they gave me into trouble. I was
sent to the Children's Panel and that was why I stopped dogging it. They
shouted at me.
</TEXT>
