<HEADLINE>#5m plan for bridge</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>2</EDITION>
<PAGE>7</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>974897160</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
A PLAN to strengthen the two towers of the Forth road bridge will cost more
than #5m.
A report which will be presented to the Forth Road Bridge Joint Board, meeting
in Glenrothes, Fife, next week, will recommend that the work go out to tender
at an estimated cost of #300,000.
Mr Bruce Grewar, the bridgemaster, will ask councillors to release the cash for
the project which will safeguard the bridge against a collision by a tanker.
The Babtie Group, which was appointed to consider the implications of the work,
has recommended a defensive structure for the piers.
</TEXT>
