<DOCNO>GH951214-000016</DOCNO>
<DOCID>GH951214-000016</DOCID>
<DATE>951214</DATE>
<HEADLINE>`Club' accused</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>1</EDITION>
<PAGE>11</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>974897169</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
ROME: Environmental campaigners have accused the ``Carbon Club'' of oil
producers of trying to block a report on global warming, which warns of
disastrous consequences if greenhouse gases are not cut. Delegates to a
UN-sponsored panel on climate change say Saudi Arabia and Kuwait are using
delaying tactics because their oil interests would be hit if the use of fossil
fuel falls.
</TEXT>
