<DATE>951214</DATE>
<HEADLINE>Killers of British mother to hang</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>3</EDITION>
<PAGE>11</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>974897199</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
Nairobi
THE brutal killers of British housewife Caron Winter were today sentenced to
death by Kenya's High Court.
The two Ugandans raped and stabbed the 31-year-old woman in her Nairobi home in
July 1994.
Caron Winter's husband, Adam, a pilot, was beaten unconscious when he arrived
home for lunch, suprising the gang. The couple's 11-month-old baby girl, Ruby,
survived unharmed.
Judge Samuel Bosire told the killers: ``I have no doubt in my mind that you
participated in the brutal murder of Mrs Caron Winter.
``It is imperative that those who caused her death should be punished
accordingly. You will therefore suffer death by hanging.''
Yusuf Rashid Wanasoro, 22, known as ``Toto'', and James Washikomba, 26, both
from Uganda, have 14 days to appeal against the sentence.
Last week three assessors found them and Kenyan Alexander Eshikavale, 37,
guilty of the rape and murder of Mrs Winter in Nairobi's affluent Karen
district.
Today the judge said he was satisfied that Wanasaro was a member of the gang
which broke into her plush suburban home to carry out a robbery in the course
of which they raped and stabbed her to death.
He said evidence against Washikomba showed ``full complicity''. However
Eshikavale was acquitted on the grounds that the case against him was provided
by a police informer who failed to give evidence in the month-long trial.
The judge said that although all the accused complained they had been tortured
and beaten up by police to force confessions, none was found to have any
injuries.
He said Wanasoro sold a video and iron box belonging to the Winters only a day
after Mrs Winter was killed.
Adam Winter and baby Ruby now live in Antigua.-Reuter.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
