<DATE>951214</DATE>
<HEADLINE>Miners to decide</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>3</EDITION>
<PAGE>4</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>974897204</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
THE miners of Monktonhall colliery in Midlothian who bought their own pit will
decide today whether or not to accept a buy-out.
Their annual general meeting will discuss a proposal from Waverley Mining
Finance, the company which wants to take over with a share offer to 200 men who
invested #10,000 of their own money in the future of the colliery. It recently
offered 10,000 ordinary shares in exchange for the miners' 51% holding.
</TEXT>
