<TEXT>
`Samurai' centre
AMBITIOUS plans for a Grampian Japanese centre based on the business exploits
of the ``Scots Samurai'' Thomas Blake Glover were taken a step further when
Grampian Regional Council's economic development and planning committee
recommended that #360,000 be found to renovate and run Braehead House at Bridge
of Don, Aberdeen. Glover founded the Mitsubishi industrial empire.
Asda go-ahead
THE go-ahead has been given for the multi-million pound redevelopment of the
Asda superstore at Garthdee in Aberdeen. Asda plans to demolish the present
store and build a replacement with new sport and recreation facilities on the
20-acre site.
Appeal lodged
PART-TIME consultant surgeon Debabarta Chatterjee, 58, who was sacked by
Western Isles Health Board, from Daliburgh Hospital, South Uist, in November
for professional misconduct has lodged an appeal with the Secretary of State
for Scotland.
Nigg proposal
A DECISION is expected within the next few days on proposals for a #15m
investment to revitalise the ailing oil fabrication yard at Nigg in Easter Ross.
