<DOCNO>GH951214-000057</DOCNO>
<DOCID>GH951214-000057</DOCID>
<DATE>951214</DATE>
<HEADLINE>REDUCED OPTIONS</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>1</EDITION>
<PAGE>12</PAGE>
<ARTICLETYPE>Features</ARTICLETYPE>
<RECORDNO>974897210</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
IT is easy to reduce the calories and fat from the Christmas Blowout and still
enjoy the meal.
n Choose a fruit starter, eg melon, or have the fish without the mayonnaise.
n Use half the amount of butter on bread, or use a low fat spread instead.
n Stick to white meat turkey, and do not eat the skin. Most of the fat is found
just under the skin. Avoid duck which is a high fat meat (50% of the calories
come from fat, compared with 8% in turkey).
n Make gravy from a stock cube rather than the meat juices.
n Make bread sauce from semi-skimmed milk rather than full fat milk.
n Have two roast potato pieces instead of four.
n Do not add extra butter to vegetables, eg buttered carrots.
n Have two glasses of wine instead of three.
n Serve Greek yoghurt on Christmas pud or mince pies. You can even mix in some
brandy and make a low fat version of brandy butter - two teaspoons of Greek
yoghurt has 85 calories, one teaspoon of regular brandy butter has 235 calories.
n Enjoy a drink but go easy - alcoholic drinks are a surprisingly high source
of calories.
</TEXT>
