<TEXT>
Palme clue
STOCKHOLM: A man dying of cancer has given a possible new clue in the unsolved
1986 murder of Swedish Prime Minister Olof Palme. Former nightclub owner Sigge
Cedergren says he gave a Smith &amp; Wesson .357 to small-time criminal Christer
Pettersson shortly before the shooting. Palme's widow picked out Pettersson as
the man who shot her husband, but he was cleared of the murder in a 1989 trial.
</TEXT>
