<HEADLINE>PR Duff's move pays off as turnover rises to #500,000</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>1</EDITION>
<PAGE>24</PAGE>
<GRAPHIC>Photograph</GRAPHIC>
<RECORDNO>974897257</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
LANARKSHIRE-based meat wholesalers PR Duff has announced a #500,000 increase in
turnover at the end of their first year in new premises in Wishaw.
Duff moved to Wishaw after 70 years in the old Glasgow Meat Market and has
expanded into new products and services.
Rory Duff, managing director, and grandson of the company's founder said: ``The
move to Lanarkshire has been very good for us.
"Our new state-of-the art premises were built by a local company and a cost of
nearly #750,000 and will allow us to grow the business in Europe.
``I am delighted to say we achieved all our goals for 1995 and we have been
able to employ additional staff.''
The company also attended the Anuega Food Fair in Germany for the first time
this year, resulting in two major new European orders valued at more than #2m.
The company's main exports are Scotch beef destined for Italy, Belgium and
Luxembourg.
</TEXT>
