Golf
JIMMY Hume, more than 40 years a professional and Alliance member, 31 years as
full pro or assistant at Gullane, and long-time club partner Eddie Wilkinson
regained the Richardson and Brownlee Salvers for the East of Scotland Golfers'
Alliance handicap foursomes at Turnhouse yesterday (Wednesday).
Hume and Wilkinson, who also won the inaugural competition in 1976 and just two
years ago, hit a three-under-par net 66 off 7 to win by half a stroke from
father and son partnership Sidney and Ian Watson (Kilspindie). Leading scores:
66 - J Hume and E Wilkinson (Gullane, 7); 66.5 - S and I Watson (Kilspindie,
