<HEADLINE>Coins or notes?</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>1</EDITION>
<PAGE>18</PAGE>
<ARTICLETYPE>Correspondence</ARTICLETYPE>
<RECORDNO>974897356</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
WHILE I welcome the proposed issue of a #2 coin it is regrettable that we have
to wait for it until 1997.
We were treated to the predictable announcement by the Royal Bank of Scotland
that this would not lead to a change in their policy for continuing with the
issue of #1 notes.
This is a mere marketing ploy which does the public no favours. Admission that
their notes get into a very bad condition when they rub up against change is
criticism enough.
I simply do not believe their claim that ``there is still a significant desire
for the #1 note in Scotland''. An independent poll would show otherwise.
T H Skeoch,
378 Glasgow Road,
Ralston, Paisley.
</TEXT>
