<TEXT>
IN his interview with Anne Simpson on the Royal Opera House funding from the
Lottery, did Jeremy Isaacs really say, ``One swan's tutu alone will cost #300''
(December 11)?
Hundreds of thousands of our people are living in damp, unhealthy conditions
and until that is righted, not one penny of lottery money should be spent
elsewhere.
Jeremy Isaacs quoted from Humperdinck's opera Hansel and Gretel:
``Oh touch me too
That I may see the world anew.''
Right.
Richard Gallagher,
13 Rowand Avenue,
Giffnock.
</TEXT>
