<EDITION>1</EDITION>
<PAGE>27</PAGE>
<ARTICLETYPE>Features</ARTICLETYPE>
<FLAG>commercial and industrial property</FLAG>
<RECORDNO>974897372</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
CONSTRUCTION has started on the third phase of a light industrial development
in Lanarkshire. Motherwell District Council is building four units totalling
some 24,000 sq.ft at its Birchwood Courtyards development on Strathclyde
Business Park. The move follows the success of the first two phases which saw
all 26 units, totalling some 75,000 sq.ft, occupied within 18 months of
completion. The latest phase marks the district council's final industrial
development before its amalgamation into North Lanarkshire Council.
Gordon Smith, head of estates at Motherwell District Council, said: ``There is
alrady tentative interest in the development from national companies looking to
increase their representation in Lanarkshire.''
The #2m development has secured #772,500 from the European Regional Development
Fund. Strathclyde Business Park is continuing to attract office space users.
Pitney Bowes and Mitel have both taken space within a recently-completed #10m
development which consists of office pavilions ranging in size from 6500 sq.ft
to 9500 sq.ft, and a 36,500 sq.ft headquarters building. The letting agent at
Strathclyde Business Park is Montagu Evans.
</TEXT>
