<TEXT>
Tomorrow is the closing date for appeals against business rates. An extension
to the normal appeals period was announced by the Secretary of State in
September. Many Scottish firms have used the extra time to lodge appeals
against their valuation, but surveyors DM Hall estimate that there are still a
considerable number which have not yet taken action.
``Give your rating surveyor a chance to see what he can achieve on your
behalf,'' said Bob Mowat of DM Hall.
